					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the third quarter of the 14th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>437 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>170</height>
										<width>120</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>110</height>
										<width>70</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>437 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 1 unfoliated older paper and 2 unfoliated parchment flyleaves and a paper flyleaf at the end), the recto of the first and the verso of the last flyleaf are covered in silk.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>55 quires: i4 (folios 1-4), ii-liv8 (folios 5-428), lv10-1 (folios 429-437). </p>
									<p>Quire numbering in Hebrew characters.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2 3" ruledLines="31" writtenLines="31">
									<p>Uniform layout. Ruling and pricking are visible.</p>
									<p>Numerous decorations:  2 full-page miniatures of the Temple implements, masoretic lists in architectural frames, masorah in micrographic design.</p>
									<p>Masorah magna usually occupies two lines of the upper and three lines of the lower margin of each page. It is frequently written in the form of ornamental design, often that of a candlestick.</p>
									<p>Exodus, Numbers, Jeremiah, Malachi, Psalms, Song of Songs, Esther and Ezra-Nehemiah begin a new column, and Leviticus and Proverbs begin a new leaf.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script, third quarter of the 14th century, punctuated. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Note of birth: Joseph, the brother of a previous owner was born on <date calendar="Hebrew">15 Nisan 5253</date> [<date calendar="Gregorian">1493</date>] (folio 437r). </p>
							<p>Illegible Hebrew inscription (folio 1r).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. 18th-century Italian red velvet binding on wood boards, with copper centrepiece and cornerpieces and remains of clasps.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Biblia Sacra Hebraica in Membrana. Mus. Brit. Jure. Emptionis. 15, 250.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
					</physDesc>
